In addition, the following @command{rpm} options, specific to the
@value{PACKAGE_TITLE} package are available:

@table @command

@item --without compat-svr4
@opindex compat-svr4

Disable source compatibility with SVR 4.2 MP variants.  This option disables the
SVR 4.2 MP compatibility functions that are included in the separate kernel
module @file{streams-svr4compat.o}.  This option defaults to enabled.

@item --without compat-sol8
@opindex compat-sol8

Disable source compatibility with Solaris 8 variants.  This option disables the
Solaris 8 compatibility functions that are included in the separate kernel
module @file{streams-suncompat.o}.  This option defaults to enabled.

@item --without compat-uw7
@opindex compat-uw7

Disable source compatibility with UnixWare 7 variants.  This option disables the
UnixWare 7 compatibility functions that are included in the separate kernel
module @file{streams-uw7compat.o}.  This option defaults to enabled.

@item --without compat-osf
@opindex compat-osf

Disable source compatibility with OSF/1.2 variants.  This option disables the
OSF/1.2 compatibility functions that are included in the separate kernel module
@file{streams-osfcompat.o}.  This option defaults to enabled.

@item --without compat-aix
@opindex compat-aix

Disable source compatibility with AIX 4 variants.  This option disables the AIX
4 compatibility functions that are included in the separate kernel module
@file{streams-aixcompat.o}.  This option defaults to enabled.

@item --without compat-hpux
@opindex compat-hpux

Disable source compatibility with HPUX variants.  This option disables the HPUX
compatibility functions that are included in the separate kernel module
@file{streams-hpuxcompat.o}.  This option defaults to enabled.

@item --without compat-lis
@opindex compat-lis

Disable source compatibility with LiS variants.  This option disables the LiS
compatibility functions that are included in the separate kernel module
@file{streams-liscompat.o}.  This option defaults to enabled.

@item --with module-sth
@itemx --without module-sth
@opindex module-sth

Enable building @file{sth} (stream head) module linked into @file{streams}
object instead built as a separate loadable kernel module.  The default is to
create the module as a separate loadable kernel module.

@item --with module-pipemod
@itemx --without module-pipemod
@opindex module-pipemod

Enable building @file{pipemod} module linked into @file{streams} object instead
built as a separate loadable kernel module.  The default is to create the module
as a separate loadable kernel module.

@item --with module-connld
@itemx --without module-connld
@opindex module-connld

Enable building @file{connld} module linked into @file{streams} object instead
built as a separate loadable kernel module.  The default is to create the module
as a separate loadable kernel module.

@item --with module-sc
@itemx --without module-sc
@opindex module-sc

Enable building @file{sc} module linked into @file{streams} object instead built
as a separate loadable kernel module.  The default is to create the module as a
separate loadable kernel module.

@item --with driver-clone
@itemx --without driver-clone
@opindex driver-clone

Enable building @file{clone} driver linked into @file{streams} object instead
built as a separate loadable kernel module.  The default is to create the driver
as a separate loadable kernel module.

@item --with driver-fifo
@itemx --without driver-fifo
@opindex driver-fifo

Enable building @file{fifo} driver linked into @file{streams} object instead
built as a separate loadable kernel module.  The default is to create the driver
